                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "So the interesting part of the crash report is that on your crash path, there is fglrx-libGL, which is libGL for the ATI card, while the intel card is the active one, not the ATI. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I guess firefox doesn't crash if you switch to the ATI card.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Mike Hommey [:glandium]", 
            "email": "Mike Hommey [:glandium]"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2011-11-22 10:55:26", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The glxtest process didn't crash, and identified the Intel Mesa driver. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The crash stack shows it's using FGLRX. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Apparently this is a dual-GPU machine and it switched from the Intel Mesa driver to the FGLRX driver at some point since Firefox was started.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
